My original plan was to have a vaginal delivery, but sometimes things don’t go the way we planned. 

I gave birth via c-section. My fiancé and I had less than 14 hrs before we became parents. 

I could go on about why I had to give birth 2 weeks early, but ultimately, we’re so glad she was delivered safely. 

There were moments of mom-shaming from a few nurses, the lactation consultant, and the hospital pediatrician. 

All of this was unexpected and shocking. Ideally, the birthing experience is supposed to be beautiful.

But for health care professionals to behave insensitively towards new parents, let alone mothers, is disturbing. 

I’m talking about it because I know I’m not the only one who’s faced something like this. It’s sad and stressful. 

I want to shine light on the realities of some of these hospitals and doctors not following the oath they swore to. 

I’m also aware that it’s not like this everywhere. And that this is my own personal experience. We had some really great healthcare professionals that took care of us, too. 

But, unfortunately, the bad outweighed the good. 

I had to learn to forgive and let go. I refused to allow that whole experience to rob me of the joy that is the newborn phase and those first few weeks of being postpartum. 

Although the recovery reminded me so much of my previous body trauma with my accident, I had to learn to separate the two. 

I’ve been loving myself, my fiancé, and my baby every day. Learning who she is, what she needs, and what we need. 

It’s the most challenging yet rewarding experience of my life. I wouldn’t have it any other way. 

Cheers to all of the parents out there who conquer so much for their little love(s). 

P.S. if I don’t call/text you back… this is what I’m doing 😬🌸
_____________________________
#newmom #motherhood #csection #recovery #postpartumjourney #sahm #hospital #healthcare

The post-wedding exhaustion is real. My family is on the mend from a bad cold and I need to put my hair away for a while lol. Especially if I catch their cooties. 

I made these DIY #doubleendeddreads last summer and have installed them 3 times now. They wash nicely and are holding up pretty good if I say so myself 😏 

I said lazy because I didn’t care to have perfect parting like I normally would when I do my box braids. Also I got lazy with the install and had some dreads bigger than others, but wH0 cArEZ. 

Install time was two movies worth and a bit of #emilyinparis #meangirls #theweddingdate (lots of stop and go).
